ippets%20that%20could%20be%20plucked%20from%20a%20courtroom%20procedural.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20Brad%20Karp%20wasn't%20trying%20to%20convince%20a%20judge.%20He%20was%20trying%20to%20show%20some%202%2C500%20employees%20that%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-weiss-trump-executive-order-agreement-language-dei-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeal%20the%20firm%20cut%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20escape%20a%20punishing%20executive%20order%20didn't%20represent%20a%20capitulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20clear%20he%20made%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20email%2C%20at%20more%20than%201%2C600%20words%2C%20appears%20to%20offer%20a%20muddled%20apology%2C%20said%20David%20Clementson%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20public%20relations%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Georgia's%20Grady%20College%20of%20Journalism%20and%20Mass%20Communication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEither%20apologize%20if%20you%20did%20something%20wrong%2C%20or%20don't%20apologize%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20email%20contains%20%26quot%3Bgradations%20of%20both.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump's%20March%2014%20executive%20order%20targeted%20Paul%20Weiss%2C%20which%20is%20known%20for%20its%20ties%20to%20Democrats%2C%20over%20the%20firm's%20diversity%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20inclusion%20policies%20and%20promised%20a%20review%20of%20its%20government%20contracts.%20The%20president%20also%20took%20aim%20in%20the%20order%20at%20a%20former%20attorney%20with%20the%20firm%2C%20Mark%20Pomerantz%2C%20who%20worked%20on%20a%20Manhattan%20district%20attorney%20inquiry%20into%20Trump's%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pressure%20from%20the%20White%20House%20resulted%20in%20an%20Oval%20Office%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2025%2F03%2F21%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fpaul-weiss-trump.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emeeting%3C%2Fa%3E%20involving%20Karp%20and%20Trump.%20Those%20talks%20yielded%20an%20agreement%20for%20the%20firm%20to%20provide%20%2440%20million%20worth%20of%20pro%20bono%20work%20to%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221ca254a2-4a7a-4a6a-bfd3-b57a0bfc5375%5C%22%3E'Hyberbolic%20langugage'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20memo%2C%20Karp%20wrote%20that%20the%20period%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bprofoundly%20unsettling%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20firm's%20employees%20and%20that%20many%20people%20at%20Paul%20Weiss%20were%20understandably%20%26quot%3Buncomfortable%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20decision%20to%20strike%20an%20agreement%20with%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20the%20executive%20order%20was%20unprecedented%20in%20the%20firm's%20150-year%20history%20and%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bcould%20easily%20have%20destroyed%20our%20firm.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClementson%2C%20who%20studies%20crisis%20communications%2C%20said%20the%20memo's%20references%20to%20an%20%26quot%3Bexistential%20crisis%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bimpossibly%20challenging%20circumstances%26quot%3B%20could%20have%20gone%20too%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20this%20high-intensity%2C%20hyperbolic%20language%2C%20which%20tends%20to%20backfire%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20shows%20people%20often%20doubt%20the%20truthfulness%20of%20a%20statement%20when%20it%20invokes%20emotional%20language%2C%20he%20said.%20In%20addition%2C%20one%20of%20the%20essential%20actions%20in%20a%20crisis%20is%20to%20project%20calm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClementson%20added%20that%20phrases%20conveying%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe're%20breaking%20the%20glass%2C%20pulling%20the%20fire%20alarm%26quot%3B%20aren't%20what%20an%20audience%20wants%20to%20hear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20Weiss%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClementson%20said%20that%20the%20situation%20would%20have%20appeared%20more%20like%20a%20victory%20for%20the%20firm%20had%20it%20gone%20to%20staffers%20sooner%20with%20a%20more%20fulsome%20defense%20of%20its%20negotiations%20with%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Sunday%20memo%2C%20which%20followed%20one%20sent%20to%20staffers%20not%20long%20after%20the%20White%20House%20issued%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-weiss-trump-executive-order-agreement-language-dei-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubsequent%20executive%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%20involving%20the%20deal%2C%20is%20likely%20an%20indication%20that%20at%20least%20some%20of%20the%20firm's%20staffers%20were%20unswayed%2C%20Kevin%20Donahue%2C%20a%2030-year%20veteran%20of%20crisis%20management%20work%20who%20is%20managing%20director%20and%20head%20of%20the%20crisis%20practice%20at%20Falls%20%26amp%3B%20Co.%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClementson%20said%20the%20firm%20needed%20to%20be%20ready%20to%20unleash%20a%20fusillade%20of%20communications%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0starting%20internally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20your%20business%20already%20knows%20that%20something%20could%20be%20hitting%20the%20fan%2C%20you%20need%20to%20get%20out%20in%20front%20of%20it%20yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c7de685f-b3b0-4d75-9042-540a47dcf203%5C%22%3EA%20bet-the-company%20moment%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20email%2C%20Karp%20wrote%20the%20money%20the%20pro%20bono%20work%20the%20firm%20agreed%20to%20do%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20Trump%20administration%20was%20in%20areas%20in%20which%20%26quot%3Bwe%20are%20already%20doing%20significant%20work.%26quot%3B%20These%20include%20helping%20veterans%2C%20fighting%20antisemitism%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bpromoting%20the%20fairness%20of%20the%20justice%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClementson%20said%20it%20would%20have%20been%20better%20for%20the%20firm%20to%20underscore%20that%20rather%20than%20fighting%20Trump's%20bottomless%20legal%20resources%2C%20it%20chose%20to%20direct%20%2440%20million%20worth%20of%20its%20resources%20to%20support%20causes%20with%20which%20it%20is%20already%20aligned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20firm's%20revenue%20topped%20more%20than%20%242.6%20billion%20in%202024%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20has%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20additional%20spending%20on%20pro%20bono%20work%20might%20represent%20only%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20revenue%20at%20risk%2C%20said%20Gina%20Rubel%2C%20CEO%20at%20Furia%20Rubel%20Communications%2C%20which%20advises%20law%20firms%20and%20their%20clients%20on%20crisis%20communications%20and%20public%20relations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20didn't%20want%20to%20have%20to%20capitulate%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Yet%2C%20the%20legal%20profession%20is%20under%20attack%2C%20Rubel%20said%2C%20and%20the%20situation%20Paul%20Weiss%20faces%20is%20indeed%20a%20%26quot%3Bbet-the-company%26quot%3B%20moment%2C%20as%20Karp%20indicated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERubel%2C%20a%20lawyer%20though%20she%20no%20longer%20practices%2C%20said%20attorneys%20often%20tell%20clients%20it's%20better%20to%20settle%20than%20to%20litigate.%20Given%20the%20amount%20of%20Paul%20Weiss%20business%20that%20could%20have%20been%20at%20risk%2C%20Karp%20appeared%20to%20have%20reached%20that%20conclusion%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20Karp%20also%20has%20a%20fiduciary%20duty%20to%20the%20firm%20to%20keep%20it%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERubel%20said%20he%20made%20that%20point%20in%20the%20memo%2C%20which%2C%20she%20said%2C%20also%20addresses%20so%20many%20of%20the%20things%20that%20people%20have%20been%20saying%20and%20speaks%20directly%20to%20the%20court%20of%20public%20opinion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDonahue%20said%20Karp%20might%20have%20succeeded%20in%20gaining%20some%20workers'%20trust%20because%20it%20made%20clear%20Paul%20Weiss%20considered%20fighting%20the%20executive%20order%20in%20court%2C%20as%20at%20least%20one%20other%20firm%20has%20done.%20Yet%2C%20ultimately%2C%20Donahue%20said%2C%20Paul%20Weiss%20concluded%20too%20many%20clients%20would%20have%20perceived%20the%20firm%20as%20persona%20n