-id%3D%5C%229542bd66-48a6-410e-a8a4-8655c224fab2%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20to%20wash%20pillows%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20wash%20pillows%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b109dbb3-e147-4df3-af95-f6e4ef592828%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20you%20need%5C%22%3EWhat%20you%20need%3C%2Fh4%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFront%20load%20washer%2Fdryer%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStain%20remover%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELaundry%20soap%20or%20detergent%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDryer%20balls%20(or%20tennis%20balls)%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%20the%20label%20for%20cleaning%20instructions.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EUnless%20otherwise%20noted%2C%20most%20down%2C%20feather%2C%20and%20polyester%20pillows%20are%20machine-washable.%20As%20a%20general%20guideline%2C%20if%20the%20pillows%20aren't%20machine-washable%2C%20they%20shouldn't%20be%20put%20in%20a%20dryer%2C%20either.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ERemove%20the%20pillow%20cover%20and%20case%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESet%20them%20aside%20to%20be%20washed%20separately.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EWash%20the%20pillow%20on%20a%20gentle%20cycle%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20most%20ideal%20scenario%20is%20a%20front-loading%20washing%20machine%2C%20because%20the%20agitator%20(the%20spindle%20in%20the%20center)%20in%20top-loading%20washers%20can%20damage%20pillows.%20If%20you're%20washing%20machine%20is%20big%20enough%2C%20wash%20two%20pillows%20at%20at%20time%20to%20balance%20out%20the%20machine.%20Avoid%20fabric%20softener%20when%20washing%20any%20and%20all%20pillows.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EDry%20the%20pillow%20thoroughly%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThis%20step%20may%20take%20the%20longest%2C%20but%20it's%20the%20most%20important.%20To%20avoid%20mildew%2C%20throw%20the%20pillow%20in%20the%20dryer%20with%20dryer%20balls%20or%20tennis%20balls%20to%20keep%20the%20filling%20from%20clumping.%20It%20may%20take%20two%20or%20three%20cycles%20to%20get%20your%20pillows%20completely%20dry.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223e40dfa9-fe5f-4201-a6cd-cc455d1aa123%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20to%20spot-treat%20pillows%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20spot-treat%20pillows%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBuckwheat%20and%20memory%20foam%20pillows%20should%20never%20cleaned%20in%20a%20washing%20machine.%20Instead%2C%20your%20best%20bet%20is%20to%20spot-treat%20any%20stains%20as%20they%20happen.%20You%20can%20use%20a%20stain%20remover%20or%20mild%20soap%20and%20water.%20To%20do%20so%2C%20saturate%20the%20stain%20and%20gently%20%26quot%3Bfeather%20the%20water%20ring%20out%20by%20using%20a%20dry%20towel%2C%20starting%20in%20the%20middle%20and%20wiping%20from%20the%20center%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20other%20pillow%20types%2C%20and%20for%20stains%20like%20blood%20or%20saliva%2C%20you%20can%20pre-treat%20them%20with%20a%20stain%20remover%20before%20washing.%20For%20yellow%20sweat%20stains%20in%20particular%2C%20Richardson%20suggests%20treating%20the%20stain%20with%20oxygen%20bleach%20added%20to%20some%20warm%20wash%20water.%20And%20if%20you're%20looking%20to%20treat%20a%20sweat-stained%20throw%20pillow%20made%20of%20wool%20or%20silk%2C%20Richardson%20says%20to%20use%20sudsy%20ammonia%20in%20lieu%20of%20oxygen%20bleach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20tip%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-74915-20%26h%3Deb1357ee2b6346b439bf58681cd9de2a4b383baa04d06d513cb117782ab2202b%26postID%3D628f975fa2374776c7e881e4%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fhow-to-wash-pillows%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FCoop-Home-Goods-Protectors-Hypoallergenic%252Fdp%252FB01LA2GXQG%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epillow%20protectors%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20both%20sleep%20and%20throw%20pillows%20to%20protect%20them%20so%20they%20don't%20have%20to%20be%20washed%20or%20dried%20as%20frequently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220718304f-cb7a-4c98-a34f-9d7e2098aa91%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20to%20keep%20pillows%20fresh%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20keep%20pillows%20fresh%20between%20deep%20cleans%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20easiest%20way%20to%20extend%20the%20life%20of%20your%20pillows%20is%20to%20invest%20in%20a%20pillow%20cover%20or%20protector.%20Not%20to%20be%20confused%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-pillowcase%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epillowcase%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20pillow%20covers%20typically%20have%20a%20zippered%20closure%20and%20are%20designed%20to%20be%20an%20added%20barrier.%20That%20way%2C%20you%20can%20simply%20just%20wash%20the%20cover%20or%20case%20more%20frequently.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAside%20from%20washing%20your%20covers%20and%20cases%20regularly%20between%20deep%20cleans%2C%20Richardson%20points%20to%20a%20not-so-obvious%2C%20yet%20very%20clever%20means%20of%20freshening%20up%20your%20beloved%20headrests%3A%20essential%20oils%20%E2%80%94%20or%20vodka.%20The%20grain-based%20liquor%20is%20an%20effective%20non-toxic%20odor%20neutralizer%20that%20doesn't%20leave%20any%20scent%20of%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEither%20spray%20%5Byour%20pillows%5D%20with%20vodka%20or%20toss%20them%20into%20the%20dryer%20with%20a%20wool%20ball%20scented%20with%20an%20essential%20oil%2C%26quot%3B%20Richardson%20says%2C%20to%20remove%20any%20built%20up%20odors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226e7162c6-a8e7-4d0f-9711-90a187ece7dc%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20often%20should%20you%20wash%20pillows%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20often%20should%20you%20wash%20pillows%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20frequently%20you%20wash%20your%20pillows%20really%20depends%20on%20how%20often%20you%20use%20them.%20Since%20bed%20pillows%20are%20used%20daily%2C%20they%20typically%20need%20to%20be%20washed%20once%20every%20season%20(or%20about%20four%20times%20per%20year)%20at%20minimum%2C%20says%20Richardson.%20Throw%20pillows%2C%20in%20comparison%2C%20can%20be%20washed%20once%20a%20year%20or%20more%20often%20if%20need%20be%2C%20depending%20on%20how%20much%20use%20they%20get%20each%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2260ae9aec-cf73-48e6-a6bc-0b693fed5a5f%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22When%20should%20you%20replace%20your%20pillows%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20should%20you%20replace%20your%20pillows%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20you've%20washed%20and%20dried%20your%20pillows%20endless%20times%20over%20the%20last%20few%20months%20or%20years%20and%20now%20they're%20just%20not%20quite%20as%20snuggly%20as%20they%20used%20to%20be%2C%20right%3F%20Well%2C%20that's%20when%20you%20know%20it's%20time%20for%20a%20swap.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can't%20fluff%20them%20back%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Richardson%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20is%20time%20to%20change%20them.%20After%20all%2C%20the%20best%20part%20of%20a%20pillow%20is%20that%20it%20is%20comfy!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20tip%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20National%20Sleep%20Foundation%20recommends%20changing%20pillows%20every%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e696b664-f57c-4c71-903c-485d22fa9bd7%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22The%20bottom%20line%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20bottom%20line%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20pillows%20%E2%80%94%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20buckwheat%20and%20memory%20%E2%80%94%20are%20machine-%20and%20dryer-friendly.%20To%20keep%20pillows%20fresh%20between%20deep%20cleans%2C%20spot%20treat%20with%20some%20soap%20and%20water%2C%20or%20spritz%20with%20a%20vodka%20or%20essential%20oil%20spray%20to%20remove%20odors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-wash-pillows%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742851615000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.inside