3Cfigcaption%3EYou'll%20want%20to%20consider%20more%20than%20thread%20count%20when%20buying%20sheets.%3Cp%3EJackal%20Pan%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThread%20count%20%E2%80%94%20referring%20to%20the%20number%20of%20yarns%20in%20a%20square%20inch%20of%20sheeting%20%E2%80%94%20has%20long%20been%20considered%20an%20easy%20way%20to%20shop%20for%20luxurious%20sheets%3A%20The%20higher%20the%20thread%20count%2C%20the%20better%20the%20bedding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20not%20necessarily%20the%20case%20because%20of%20the%20way%20some%20brands%20count%20yarns.%20Plus%2C%20not%20all%20types%20of%20sheets%20use%20thread%20count%20as%20a%20designator%20of%20quality.%20Manufacturers%20of%20cotton%20sheets%20list%20the%20thread%20count%2C%20but%20you%20won't%20always%20find%20a%20number%20on%20your%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-linen-sheets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20linen%20sheets%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20example.%20Here's%20what%20you%20need%20to%20know%20about%20sheet%20thread%20counts%2C%20and%20why%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-sheets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20best%20sheets%3C%2Fa%3E%20don't%20always%20have%20the%20highest%20thread%20count.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aa8db915-c5d4-4b40-bd16-6172b6061100%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20is%20thread%20count%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20thread%20count%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Illustration%20of%20side%20by%20side%20comparison%20of%20percale%20and%20sateen%2C%20two%20types%20of%20cotton%20weave%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F614355aa2db0850019a9c4a6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221036%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20a%20percale%20weave%2C%20one%20yarn%20is%20woven%20with%20another%20thread%20into%20a%20tight%20grid%20pattern.%20It's%20a%20%26quot%3Bone%20under%2C%20one%20over%26quot%3B%20pattern.%20In%20a%20sateen%20weave%2C%20three%20or%20four%20threads%20are%20woven%20over%20one%20thread%20into%20a%20looser%20grid%20pattern.%20It's%20a%20%26quot%3Bthree%20over%2C%20one%20under%26quot%3B%20weave%20pattern.%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Powell%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWoven%20fabric%20is%20made%20of%20horizontal%20(weft)%20and%20vertical%20(warp)%20yarns.%20If%20a%20piece%20of%20fabric%20has%20100%20warp%20yarns%20and%20100%20weft%20yarns%20in%20a%20square%20inch%2C%20it%20would%20be%20a%20200-thread-count%20sheet.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20people%20often%20associate%20higher%20thread%20counts%20with%20luxury%20is%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20yarn.%20Finer%20threads%20feel%20silkier%2C%20and%20you%20can%20weave%20more%20into%20a%20square%20inch%20than%20a%20thicker%20yarn.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20woven%20pattern%20also%20factors%20into%20the%20thread%20count.%20For%20percale%20sheets%2C%20the%20pattern%20alternates%20with%20a%20thread%20going%20over%20then%20under%2C%20over%20then%20under.%20In%20a%20sateen%20weave%2C%20threads%20skip%20over%20three%20or%20four%20yarns%2C%20then%20go%20under%20one.%20The%20result%20is%20a%20denser%2C%20smoother%20fabric%20than%20a%20light%20and%20crisp%20percale.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESateen%20sheets%20often%20have%20a%20higher%20thread%20count%20because%20it's%20easier%20to%20fit%20more%20yarns%20into%20the%20looser%20grid%20pattern.%20For%20a%20deeper%20dive%20on%20this%2C%20check%20out%20our%20guide%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fpercale-vs-sateen-cotton-comparison%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epercale%20vs.%20sateen%20cotton%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2207ae3b63-138c-456b-a0cd-7d16af9daf24%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Are%20higher%20thread-count%20sheets%20better%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20higher%20thread-count%20sheets%20better%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20necessarily.%20%26quot%3BYou%20see%20sometimes%20sheets%20advertised%20for%20ungodly%20numbers%20of%20high%20thread%20counts%2C%20and%20you%20think%2C%20'How%20can%20they%20possibly%20fit%20600%20threads%20into%20this%20little%20bit%20of%20sheet%3F'%26quot%3B%20said%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.human.cornell.edu%2Fpeople%2Ffhk2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFran%20Kozen%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20senior%20lecturer%20and%20director%20of%20undergraduate%20studies%20at%20Cornell's%20Department%20of%20Human%20Centered%20Design.%C2%A0%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20take%20two%20yarns%20and%20spin%20them%20together%2C%20you'll%20make%20what's%20called%20a%20ply%20yarn.%20%26quot%3BThat%20makes%20a%20stronger%20yarn%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kozen%2C%20and%20sheets%20can%20be%20made%20with%20single-%2C%20double-%2C%20triple%20ply%20yarns.%C2%A0%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20manufacturer%20could%20use%20a%20double-ply%20yarn%20and%20have%20100%20yarns%20going%20in%20the%20weft%20and%20warp%20directions%20but%20count%20it%20as%20a%20400-thread-count%20sheet%20instead%20of%20200.%20%26quot%3BSo%20when%20you%20see%20something%20that%20says%20it's%20a%20600-thread-count%20sheet%2C%20my%20suspicion%20is%20that%20they're%20counting%20plies%20because%20I%20can't%20really%20see%20that%20you%20could%20fit%20300%20yards%20in%20it%20per%20inch%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kozen.%C2%A0%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20resulting%20sheet%20might%20have%20poor%20airflow%20and%20wouldn't%20necessarily%20feel%20more%20luxurious%20than%20400-thread-count%20fabric%20with%20finer%2C%20single-ply%20yarn.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20tip%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBetween%20300%20to%20400%20is%20typically%20a%20good%20range%20for%20thread%20count.%20Above%20that%2C%20manufacturers%20are%20counting%20plied%20thread.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d9521363-1015-48ce-8fc1-68a9c80780f5%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What's%20a%20good%20thread%20count%20for%20sheets%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20a%20good%20thread%20count%20for%20sheets%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20find%20very%20nice%20sheets%20at%20between%20300%20to%20400%20thread%20counts%2C%20but%20you%20may%20also%20find%20soft%2C%20durable%20sheets%20outside%20this%20range.%20However%2C%20this%20isn't%20the%20only%20marker%20of%20quality.%20You'll%20also%20want%20to%20look%20for%20the%20type%20of%20cotton%20used%20in%20the%20sheets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKozen%20recommends%20looking%20for%20long-staple%20cotton%20and%20those%20labeled%20pima%20(or%20Supima)%2C%20Peruvian%2C%20or%20Egyptian%20cotton.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20they%20give%20a%20name%20to%20the%20cotton%2C%20a%20varietal%20cotton%2C%20they're%20typically%20trying%20to%20tell%20you%20it's%20a%20premium%20cotton%2C%20which%20implies%20longer%20fibers%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kozen.%20Longer%20cotton%20fibers%20means%20fewer%20ends%20that%20are%20liable%20to%20protrude%2C%20so%20the%20sheets%20will%20feel%20smoother%20and%20be%20more%20durable.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeep%20in%20mind%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadnas.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fthe_truth_about_testing_processes_for_premium_cotton_for_htt_may_2016.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearchers%20have%20found%20instances%20of%20fraud%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20manufacturers%20labeled%20sheets%20as%20Egyptian%20cotton%20even%20if%20they%20were%20blended%20with%20other%20fibers%20or%20didn't%20contain%20premium%20long-staple%20cotton.%20Stick%20with%20reputable%20brands%20and%20be%20suspicious%20of%20bargain-priced%20sheets%20that%20claim%20to%20be%20100-percent%20long-staple%2C%20premium%20cotton.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222582e78a-e5f2-4ac0-bfbb-a82df87f