the%20transfer%20of%20Justice%20Varma%20to%20the%20Allahabad%20High%20Court%2C%20Mr%20Rohatgi%20said%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bmystified%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20announcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20a%20press%20note%20on%20Friday%20said%20the%20transfer%20process%20of%20Justice%20Varma%20was%20unrelated%20to%20the%20inquiry%20into%20the%20alleged%20cash%20stash%20row.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERead%20Mr%20Rohatgi's%20interview%20to%20NDTV%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQ%3A%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20transferred%20Justice%20Verma%20to%20his%20parent%20court%2C%20which%20is%20the%20Allahabad%20High%20Court.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20the%20transfer%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20cash%20stash%20case.%20How%20are%20you%20viewing%20this%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20have%20never%20understood%20the%20statement%20that%20this%20transfer%20proposal%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20cash%20scam.%20According%20to%20me%2C%20it%20is%20because%20of%20the%20cash%20scam%20that%20he%20is%20being%20proposed%20to%20be%20transferred...%20Ultimately%2C%20the%20point%20of%20the%20transfer%20is%20not%20that%20important%20because%20he%20doesn't%20have%20any%20judicial%20work.%20So%20whether%20he%20sits%20in%20his%20house%20in%20Delhi%20or%20whether%20he%20sits%20in%20his%20house%20in%20Allahabad%2C%20what%20difference%20will%20it%20make%3F%20The%20real%20question%20is%20that%20we%20should%20come%20to%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20issue%20as%20early%20as%20possible%20whether%20the%20judge%20is%20a%20delinquent%2C%20is%20he%20guilty%20of%20moral%20turpitude%2C%20or%20he%20is%20not%20and%20his%20reputation%20is%20being%20damned.%20There%20are%20several%20loose%20ends%20in%20this%20case%20as%20of%20now%20which%20need%20to%20be%20answered.%20So%20I%20don't%20think%20there%20is%20any%20great%20thing%20in%20saying%20that%20the%20transfer%20is%20not%20connected%20to%20the%20scam.%20I'm%20actually%20mystified%20by%20this%20statement%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQ%3A%20The%20issue%20has%20reached%20parliament.%20MPs%20are%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20had%20the%20person%20been%20a%20non-judge%2C%20any%20other%20citizen%2C%20a%20politician%20or%20a%20bureaucrat%2C%20then%20it%20would%20have%20led%20to%20a%20criminal%20investigation.%20Does%20it%20really%20stop%20at%20an%20investigation%20which%20is%20clearly%20an%20in-house%20investigation%20by%20the%20judiciary%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20No.%20Please%20understand%20and%20your%20viewers%20also%20must%20understand.%20The%20position%20of%20a%20judge%20is%20entirely%20different%20from%20a%20bureaucrat%20or%20a%20police%20officer.%20Why%3F%20Because%20a%20judge%20decides%20cases%20day%20in%20and%20day%20out.%20Everyday%20one%20party%20to%20a%20case%20is%20dissatisfied%20and%20unhappy%20with%20the%20decision%20because%20the%20decision%20has%20gone%20against%20one%20party.%20So%20there%20is%20a%20natural%20reaction%20in%20our%20country%20which%20is%20full%20of%20cynics%20that%20the%20judge%20may%20have%20been%20bought%20over%20or%20is%20won%20over%20by%20one%20party%20or%20the%20other.%20A%20large%20number%20of%20complaints%20are%20made%20everyday%20against%20every%20judge%2C%20whether%20of%20the%20first%20court%2C%20second%20court%2C%20high%20court%2C%20or%20Supreme%20Court.%20And%20therefore%2C%20you%20can't%20start%20a%20police%20investigation%20in%20every%20case%20where%20people%20file%20such%20complaints.%20A%20judge%20cannot%20fearlessly%20be%20independent%20when%20these%20swords%2C%20several%20swords%20are%20hanging%20on%20his%20heads.%20Parliament%20in%20its%20wisdom%20talked%20about%20impeachment.%20There%20is%20an%20in-house%20procedure%20for%20looking%20at%20some%20of%20these%20sensitive%20complaints.%2099%20per%20cent%20complaints%20are%20thrown%20in%20the%20dustbin.%20But%20some%20complaints%20do%20merit%20some%20prima%20facie%20investigation%20or%20maybe%20a%20full-blown%20investigation.%20Now%20that%20is%20left%20to%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20or%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20to%20decide%20because%20you%20know%20otherwise%20the%20system%20of%20justice%20will%20come%20to%20an%20end.%20It%20is%20this%20difference%20which%20makes%20a%20difference%20between%20the%20judiciary%20and%20other%20wings%20of%20the%20executive%20or%20even%20parliament.%20This%20is%20how%20we%20must%20perceive%20it.%20I%20am%20not%20for%20a%20moment%20trying%20to%20say%20that%20anybody%20is%20above%20the%20law.%20Even%20a%20judge%20can%20be%20prosecuted%2C%20but%20it%20requires%20a%20nod%20from%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India.%20This%20was%20settled%20in%20a%20famous%20case%20of%20a%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20called%20K%20Veeraswami%20case.%20So%20that's%20how%20it%20goes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQ%3A%20Visuals%20of%20the%20burnt%20cash%20are%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20and%20they%20have%20tarnished%20the%20image%20of%20the%20judiciary.%20What%20measures%20do%20you%20think%20the%20judiciary%20must%20take%20to%20restore%20public%20faith%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20First%2C%20about%20the%20recovery%20of%20cash.%20Now%20where%20is%20that%20recovery%3F%20There%20is%20no%20recovery.%20There%20is%20no%20evidence.%20The%20entire%20evidence%20if%20at%20all%20has%20been%20destroyed%20by%20the%20police%2C%20by%20the%20fire%20department.%20There%20were%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Rs%20500%20notes%20which%20I%20saw%20very%20clearly%20in%20the%20video%20and%20I%20have%20seen%20better%20pictures%20including%20in%20the%20Free%20Press%20Journal%20Mumbai%20edition%20this%20morning.%20So%20where%20are%20those%20notes%3F%20Where%20have%20they%20gone%3F%20Even%20if%20Rs%205%20lakh%20is%20found%20in%20the%20office%20of%20a%20junior%20engineer%2C%20it%20is%20seized%20immediately%2C%20income%20tax%20officials%20take%20over.%20What%20happened%20in%20this%20case%3F%20The%20police%20commissioner%20was%20aware.%20The%20next%20morning%2C%20everything%20is%20over.%20No%20evidence%20is%20found.%20It's%20only%20rubbish%20there.%20They%20say%20it%20was%20thrown%20with%20garbage.%20So%20what%20kind%20of%20job%20has%20the%20police%20done%3F%20I%20am%20amazed.%20Can%20you%20have%20a%20case%20of%20corruption%20where%20it%20is%20%5Bcaught%5D%20red-handed%2C%20kind%20of%20red-handed%20where%20money%20is%20found%2C%20but%20there%20is%20no%20money%3F%20So%20that%20is%20one%20part%20of%20the%20case%20but%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20comment%20any%20further%20on%20that.%20Investigation%20will%20tell%20us%20and%20you%20need%20a%20police%20investigation%2C%20not%20an%20investigation%20by%20three%20judges.%20That%20cannot%20help.%20You%20need%20a%20forensic%20investigation.%20Large%20number%20of%20CDRs%20(call%20detail%20records)%2C%20large%20number%20of%20CCTV%20footage%2C%20different%20personnel%20of%20police%2C%20fire%20department%2C%20NDMC%2C%20CRPF%2C%20all%20that%20has%20to%20be%20kind%20of%20collated%20and%20examined.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20the%20second%20question%2C%20obviously%20it's%20a%20huge%20dent%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20justice%20dispensation%20system%20where%20people%20see%20this%20kind%20of%20thing%20and%20if%20the%20judge%20is%20guilty%2C%20strict%20action%20should%20be%20taken%20at%20the%20earliest.%20The%20larger%20issue%20is%20the%20old%20debate%20of%20the%20manner%20of%20appointment%20of%20judges%20and%20the%20manner%20of%20disciplinary%20proceedings%20against%20judges.%20They%20have%20to%20be%20re-looked%20at.%20The%20appointment%20system%20of%20the%20collegium%20is%20completely%20unsatisfactory%20and%20opaque.%20That%20was%20not%20what%20the%20Constitution%20said.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20interpreted%20the%20Constitution%20somewhat%20selectively%20in%20its%20judgment%20where%20consultation%20with%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20has%20become%20concurrence%20of%20the%20Chief%20Justice.%20I%20am%20sure%20there%20is%20a%20clear%20difference%20between%20the%20two%20words%2C%20but%20that's%20how%20the%20judgment%20stands.%20So%20the%20attempt%20to%20bring%20in%20some%20sunlight%20was%20by%20the%20NJAC%20(National%20Judicial%20Appointments%20Commission)%20Act%2010%20years%20ago.%20That%20was%20shut%20down%20by%20the%20court.%20The%20court%20did%20not%20want%20to%20give%20up%20the%20power%20of%20appointment.%20All%20right%2C%20if%20the%20NJAC%20was%20banned%2C%20we%20can%20have%20some%20sunlight%20via%20the%20media%2C%20some%20outsiders%20in%20a%20committee%20which%20should%20recommend%20judges%20and%20not%20only%20judges%20selecting%20judges.%20Anyway%2C%20that's%20one%20debate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20issue%20is%20we%20must%20have%20a%20better%20system%20for%20purposes%20of%20disciplinary%20action.%20Today%2C%20the%20only%20action%20under%20the%20Constitution%20is%20impeachment.%20Impeachment%20is%20so%20laborious%2C%20complex%20and%20difficult%20that%20no%20impeachment%20has%20happened%20in%20the%20last%2075%20years.%20You%20need%20100%20MPs%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20to%20start%20action%20for%20impeachment.%20Then%20it%20requires%20an%20admission%20order%20by%20the%20Speaker%20because%20some%20material%20has%20to%20be%20shown.%20That%20requires%20a%20debate.%20Then%20it%20requires%20a%20full-blown%20inquiry%20of%20judges%20being%20members%20of%20a%20committee%20appointed%20by%20the%20Speaker.%20That's%20a%20full-blown%20inquiry%20where%20examination%2C%20cross-examination%2C%20production%20of%20documents%2C%20etc%20is%20there.%20After%20that%2C%20the%20matter%20has%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20house%20for%20debate.%20Then%20in%20that%20debate%2C%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20MPs%20have%20to%20approve%20the%20motion%20and%20the%20motion%20has%20to%20be%20in%20that%20session%20alone.%20So%20you%20know%20parliament%2C%20government%20and%20stakeholders%20including%20public%2C%20lawyers%20etc%20must%20bring%20about%20a%20consensus%20to%20remove%20this%20so-called%20impeachment%20system%2C%20bring%20in%20a%20more%20smoother%20system%20and%20manners%20of%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQ%3A%20You%20want%20the%20impeachment%20system%20to%20be%20done%20away%20with%20to%20bring%20a%20system%20that's%20faster%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20No%2C%20because%20ultimately%20the%20proof%20of%20the%20pudding%20is%20in%20eating.%20Yes.%20Three%20or%20four%20attempts%20of%20impeachment%20have%20been%20made%20in%20the%20last%2070%20years.%20Nothing%20has%20succeeded.%20Nothing%20has%20come%20to%20fruition.%20Therefore%2C%20you%20have%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20that%20system.%20Times%20have%20changed.%20Bring%20a%20new%20system%2C%20a%20faster%20system%20because%20the%20justice%20system%20cannot%20afford%20any%20delay.%20If%20the%20dispenser%20of%20justice%20is%20himself%20under%20a%20cloud%2C%20what%20kind%20of%20justice%20will%20be%20dispensed%3F%20But%20I%20must%20tell%20you%20one%20thing%2C%20I%20am%20very%20happy%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20this%20case%20%5Bjudge%20cash%20row%5D%20has%20been%20more%20transparent%20than%20it%20has%20been%20in%20the%20past.%20Everything%20is%20now%20in%20public%20domain%20and%20I%20think%20hats%20off%20to%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20for%20taking%20such%20a%20courageous%20stand%20for%20showing%20everything%20to%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQ%3A%20This%20incident%20has%20highlighted%20the%20need%20for%20greater%20transparency%20and%20accountability%20within%20the%20judiciary.%20There%20are%20unanswered%20questions%20including%20the%20source%20of%20that%20cash.%20How%20did%20it%20reach%20that%20house%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20As%20Justice%20Verma%20said%2C%20when%20that%20explanation%20was%20sought%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20DK%20Upadhyaya%20of%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%2C%20he%20said%20that%20the%20cash%20doesn't%20belong%20to%20him.%20So%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20questions%20that%20have%20to%20be%20answered.%20First%20thing%2C%20where%20is%20the%20cash%3F%20Where%20are%20the%20burnt%20notes%3F%20That's%20the%20first%20thing.%20The%20second%20thing%20is%2C%20you%20examine%20the%20CCTV%20of%20the%20last%20three%20months.%20How%20was%20that%20room%20accessed%3F%20Did%20it%20have%20a%20lock%3F%20Who%20had%20the%20key%20if%20it%20was%20locked%3F%20CCTV%20would%20show%20how%20it%20was%20accessed.%20It%20may%20also%20show%20sacks%20coming%20in%20because%20sacks%20are%20not%20something%20you%20put%20in%20your%20pocket.%20How%20could%20sacks%20come%20in%3F%20The%20CRPF%20is%20at%20the%20house%20of%20every%20judge.%20It's%20not%20that%20simple%20that%20you%20bring%20in%20sacks.%20So%20what%20was%20in%20the%20sacks%3F%20Were%20they%20notes%3F%20What%20was%20it%3F%20I%20don't%20know.%20Today%20the%20material%20is%20gone.%20You%20require%20circumstantial%20evidence%20because%20the%20primary%20evidence%20is%20gone.%20But%20whatever%20it%20is%2C%20get%20down%20to%20the%20bottom%20of%20it%20at%20the%20earliest%20is%20what%20I%20would%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQ%3A%20These%20are%20allegations%20of%20corruption%20within%20the%20judiciary%2C%20so%20something%20has%20to%20be%20done%20from%20within%20the%20judiciary%20to%20protect%20the%20reputation%20of%20judges%20as%20well%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Obviously%2C%20as%20I%20said%2C%20bring%20in%20a%20more%20transparent%20system%2C%20starting%20with%20appointments%20and%20going%20on%20to%20disciplinary%20systems.%20Transparency%20is%20possible%20only%20if%20you%20let%20some%20sunlight%20in.%20Bring%20some%20outsiders%2C%20people%20on%20public%20platforms%20of%20high%20integrity.%20You%20could%20even%20have%20a%20statesman-like%20person%2C%20you%20could%20have%20an%20author%2C%20you%20could%20have%20a%20Nobel%20laureate%2C%20you%20could%20have%20a%20Bharat%20Ratna%2C%20you%20could%20have%20some%20of%20those%20people.%20It%20will%20instill%20confidence%20because%20otherwise%20people%20generally%20say%2C%20oh%2C%20judges%20are%20appointing%20judges%2C%20they%20are%20appointing%20the%20relative%20of%20a%20judge%20known%20to%20them.%20All%20this%20kind%20of%20talk%20is%20going%20on.%20To%20remove%20all%20this%2C%20you%20must%20have%20sunlight%2C%20which%20is%20the%20best%20disinfectant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQ%3A%20As%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Bar%2C%20how%20do%20you%20look%20at%20Allahabad%20High%20Court%20lawyers'%20move%20to%20protest%20against%20the%20transfer%20of%20Justice%20Varma%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20think%20it%20is%20too%20hasty%20a%20decision%20because%20I%20am%20still%20not%20very%20convinced%20in%20my%20mind%2C%20as%20of%20today%2C%20and%20as%20the%20facts%20are%20placed%20today%2C%20that%20it's%20an%20open%20and%20shut%20case.%20I%20don't%20think%20one%20should%20start%20off%20with%20these%20kinds%20of%20remarks%20off%20the%20cuff.%20Let%20us%20see%20what%20material%20is%20brought%20out%2C%20let%20us%20see%20what%20this%20committee%20reports%2C%20and%20then%20we%20should%20take%20a%20call.%20And%20as%20it%20is%2C%20work%20has%20been%20withdrawn%20from%20the%20judge.%20As%20I%20said%20in%20the%20beginning%2C%20what%20difference%20does%20it%20make%20whether%20he%20stays%20in%20his%20house%20in%20Delhi%20or%20Allahabad.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742831520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fgjb3es9g_mukul-rohatgi_625x300_24_March_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fseveral-loose-ends-need-answers-says-mukul-rohatgi-on-judge-cash-case-8000595%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Former%20Attorney%20General%20of%20India%20Mukul%20Rohatgi%20called%20for%20a%20thorough%20investigation%20into%20allegations%20that%20a%20cash%20stash%20was%20found%20on%20the%20premises%20of%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20judge%20Justice%20Yashwant%20Varma.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%