on%20case%20with%20Sebi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742824968000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fdic-india-pays-rs-34-32l-to-settle-disclosure-norm-violation-case-with-sebi-125032401084_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22DIC%20India%2C%20a%20manufacturer%20of%20printing%20inks%20and%20allied%20products%2C%20had%20filed%20suo%20motu%20settlement%20applications%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20Sebi's%20(Settlement%20Proceedings)%20regulations%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Delimitation%3A%20Don't%20Let%20Politics%20Get%20In%20The%20Way%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20as%20defined%20under%20Article%201%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9CUnion%20of%20States%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20phrase%20deliberately%20chosen%20by%20the%20framers%20to%20signify%20its%20indestructible%20nature.%20Unlike%20a%20federation%20formed%20through%20voluntary%20association%20of%20sovereign%20units%2C%20India's%20structure%20is%20quasi-federal%2C%20where%20sovereignty%20is%20indivisibly%20vested%20in%20the%20Union%2C%20though%20power%20is%20devolved%20constitutionally%20to%20the%20States%20under%20Schedules%20VII%20and%20XI-XII.%20The%20Sarkaria%20Commission%20(1988)%20and%20the%20Punchhi%20Commission%20(2010)%20further%20explored%20this%20dynamic%2C%20noting%20that%20while%20States%20enjoy%20significant%20functional%20autonomy%2C%20the%20Union%20retains%20overriding%20authority%2C%20especially%20under%20Articles%20256%2C%20356%2C%20and%20Parliament's%20residuary%20powers%20under%20Article%20248.%20This%20constitutional%20design%20ensures%20unity%20in%20diversity%20while%20allowing%20decentralised%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Complaint%20In%20The%20South%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20recent%20developments%20suggest%20a%20deliberate%20political%20engineering%20of%20Centre-State%20fissures.%20Over%20the%20past%20weeks%2C%20the%20sparring%20between%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Chief%20Minister%20MK%20Stalin%20and%20the%20Centre%20has%20amplified%20narratives%20on%20education%20policy%2C%20language%20imposition%2C%20fiscal%20devolution%2C%20and%20regional%20economic%20disparities%2C%20reinforcing%20a%20North%20vs.%20South%20dichotomy.%20The%20latest%20in%20this%20series%20is%20delimitation%2C%20where%20Stalin%20has%20positioned%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20and%20by%20extension%2C%20Southern%20states%2C%20as%20victims%20of%20an%20unjust%20reapportionment%20exercise%20that%20he%20says%20penalises%20them%20for%20their%20demographic%20prudence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20Delimitation%20Commission%2C%20whenever%20constituted%2C%20will%20face%20an%20exceptionally%20delicate%20task%2C%20balancing%20constitutional%20mandates%2C%20demographic%20realities%2C%20and%20political%20sensitivities.%20The%20core%20challenge%20lies%20in%20reconciling%20Article%2081's%20principle%20of%20population-proportional%20representation%20with%20the%20regional%20disparities%20arising%20from%20differential%20fertility%20rates%20and%20demographic%20transitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20It%20All%20Started%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20constitutional%20basis%20for%20delimitation%20in%20India%20lies%20in%20Article%2081%2C%20which%20outlines%20how%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20are%20divided%20into%20territorial%20constituencies%2C%20ensuring%20that%20the%20ratio%20of%20seats%20to%20population%20is%20the%20same%20for%20each%20state%20and%20the%20number%20of%20people%20per%20constituency%20is%20constant%20within%20a%20state.%20Similarly%2C%20Article%20170(3)%20mandates%20the%20periodic%20readjustment%20of%20State%20Legislative%20Assembly%20constituencies.%20The%20process%20is%20further%20governed%20by%20laws%20enacted%20by%20the%20Parliament%2C%20primarily%20the%20Delimitation%20Act%2C%202002.%20India%20has%20had%20Delimitation%20Commissions%20constituted%20in%201952%2C%201963%2C%201973%2C%20and%202002.%20However%2C%20this%20regular%2010-year%20cycle%20was%20interrupted%20by%20the%2042nd%20Constitution%20Amendment%20Act%2C%201976%2C%20which%20froze%20the%20population%20figures%20to%20the%201971%20census%20and%20deferred%20further%20delimitation%20until%202000.%20This%20freeze%20was%20later%20extended%20until%202026%20by%20the%2084th%20Amendment%20Act%2C%202001%2C%20as%20a%20measure%20to%20encourage%20states%20to%20pursue%20population%20stabilisation.%20The%20last%20major%20delimitation%20exercise%20in%20India%20was%20based%20on%20the%202001%20census%20figures%20and%20was%20conducted%20around%202008%2C%20after%20a%20gap%20of%20about%2030%20years%20since%20the%20previous%20one.%20This%20exercise%2C%20while%20not%20increasing%20the%20total%20number%20of%20seats%2C%20redrew%20the%20boundaries%20of%20constituencies%20within%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELooking%20ahead%20to%202026%2C%20the%20constitutional%20freeze%20on%20delimitation%20based%20on%20the%201971%20census%20is%20set%20to%20expire.%20This%20means%20that%20a%20fresh%20delimitation%20exercise%20is%20widely%20anticipated%2C%20likely%20based%20on%20the%20population%20figures%20of%20the%20next%20census%20(this%20is%20also%20an%20issue%20as%20the%20census%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20carried%20out).%20This%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20redistribution%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20State%20Assembly%20seats%20among%20states%20to%20reflect%20the%20significant%20demographic%20changes%20since%201971.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EImbalances%20Will%20Pinch%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202026%20delimitation%20exercise%20can%20potentially%20expose%20and%20exacerbate%20several%20fissures%20within%20Indian%20federalism%2C%20primarily%20stemming%20from%20the%20uneven%20patterns%20of%20population%20growth%20across%20states%20since%20the%20last%20delimitation%20exercise%20based%20on%20the%201971%20census%20for%20seat%20allocation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirstly%2C%20a%20significant%20point%20of%20contention%20revolves%20around%20political%20representation%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20States%20that%20have%20achieved%20greater%20success%20in%20population%20control%2C%20predominantly%20in%20the%20South%2C%20fear%20a%20reduction%20in%20their%20number%20of%20parliamentary%20seats%20if%20delimitation%20is%20based%20on%20current%20population%20figures.%20This%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20perceived%20imbalance%20of%20political%20power%2C%20where%20states%20with%20larger%20populations%2C%20primarily%20in%20the%20north%2C%20gain%20more%20seats%2C%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20Southern%20states.%20This%20situation%20can%20create%20a%20North-South%20divide%20in%20terms%20of%20political%20influence%20within%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20the%20potential%20redistribution%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20also%20has%20implications%20for%20state%20finances.%20Given%20India's%20fiscal%20centralisation%2C%20states%20rely%20on%20the%20Union%20government%20for%20significant%20revenue.%20Strong%20political%20representation%20in%20Parliament%20is%20seen%20as%20vital%20for%20securing%20adequate%20financial%20resources.%20A%20reduction%20in%20parliamentary%20seats%20could%20therefore%20lead%20to%20anxieties%20among%20certain%20states%20that%20their%20ability%20to%20advocate%20for%20and%20receive%20sufficient%20financial%20allocations%20from%20the%20Centre%20might%20be%20weakened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThirdly%2C%20the%20delimitation%20exercise%20could%20amplify%20existing%20regional%2C%20linguistic%2C%20and%20socio-economic%20disparities.%20If%20states%20with%20higher%20population%20growth%20are%20also%20those%20lagging%20in%20socio-economic%20indicators%2C%20an%20increase%20in%20their%20parliamentary%20representation%20might%20be%20perceived%20by%20other%20states%20as%20further%20marginalising%20their%20concerns%20and%20priorities%20within%20the%20national%20political%20discourse.%20The%20issue%20could%20take%20on%20linguistic%20dimensions%20if%20states%20with%20a%20higher%20proportion%20of%20Hindi%20speakers%20gain%20more%20influence%2C%20potentially%20exacerbating%20sensitivities%20in%20non-Hindi-speaking%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20Straight%20Road%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20how%20will%20the%20delimitation%20commission%20deal%20with%20this%20issue%3F%20The%20easiest%20and%20lazy%20way%20to%20deal%20with%20this%20issue%20is%20to%20further%20postpone%20the%20delimitation%20exercise%20and%20freeze%20it%20again%20for%20another%20few%20decades.%20This%20is%20precisely%20what%20is%20being%20suggested%20by%20MK%20Stalin.%20This%20solution%2C%20while%20convenient%20for%20everyone%2C%20has%20its%20own%20issues.%20Consider%20a%20scenario%20where%20two%20constituencies%20send%20one%20MP%20each%20to%20Parliament.%20If%20one%20constituency%20has%201%20million%20voters%20and%20another%20has%202%20million%2C%20a%20vote%20in%20the%20smaller%20constituency%20has%20twice%20the%20impact%20in%20electing%20a%20representative%20as%20a%20vote%20in%20the%20larger%20one.%20This%20imbalance%20contradicts%20the%20democratic%20principle%20of%20equal%20representation%2C%20where%20every%20citizen's%20vote%20should%20influence%20election%20outcomes%20equally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20solution%20could%20be%20to%20increase%20the%20total%20number%20of%20seats%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20proportionally%2C%20ensuring%20that%20states%20retain%20their%20existing%20representation%20while%20accommodating%20demographic%20changes.%20This%20method%20aims%20to%20prevent%20the%20dilution%20of%20political%20influence%20for%20states%20that%20have%20successfully%20implemented%20population%20control%20measures%2C%20thereby%20maintaining%20the%20current%20balance%20of%20power.%20But%20again%2C%20the%20problem%20with%20this%20is%20what%20has%20been%20already%20discussed.%20The%20proportion%20of%20seats%20held%20by%20Northern%20states%20(Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Bihar%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20etc.)%20would%20still%20increase%20more%20than%20that%20of%20Southern%20states%20(Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Kerala%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Telangana)%2C%20given%20the%20differential%20population%20growth.%20This%20would%20still%20mean%20a%20relative%20erosion%20of%20influence%20for%20states%20that%20successfully%20controlled%20their%20population.%20The%20Rajya%20Sabha%20is%20currently%20a%20counterbalancing%20force%2C%20with%20seats%20allocated%20based%20on%20states'%20existing%20political%20weight.%20If%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20expands%20disproportionately%20in%20favour%20of%20high-population%20states%2C%20Southern%20states%20could%20demand%20an%20expansion%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%20powers%20to%20counterbalance%20the%20demographic%20shift.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20Room%20For%20Missteps%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERevising%20Article%2082%20to%20incorporate%20non-population-based%20criteria%2C%20such%20as%20per%20capita%20income%2C%20literacy%20rates%2C%20healthcare%20outcomes%2C%20and%20infrastructure%20development%2C%20into%20the%20delimitation%20process%20could%20align%20political%20representation%20with%20governance%20rather%20than%20mere%20demographic%20weight.%20This%20would%20mitigate%20the%20moral%20hazard%20problem%2C%20where%20high-fertility%20states%20accrue%20disproportionate%20representation%20and%20fiscal%20benefits%20without%20undertaking%20structural%20reforms.%20A%20parallel%20exists%20in%20the%20Finance%20Commission's%20devolution%20formula%2C%20which%20factors%20in%20governance%20metrics%20to%20allocate%20resources.%20Extending%20this%20principle%20to%20parliamentary%20representation%20would%20encourage%20lagging%20states%20to%20invest%20in%20economic%20productivity%20and%20social%20development.%20Such%20a%20framework%20can%20nudge%20Northern%20states%20towards%20institutional%20and%20policy%20reforms%2C%20ensuring%20that%20seat%20allocation%20reflects%20developmental%20performance%20rather%20than%20sheer%20population%20growth.%20This%20will%20help%20in%20preserving%20federal%20equilibrium%20while%20enhancing%20national%20governance%20standards.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIrrespective%20of%20whatever%20approach%20is%20adopted%2C%20this%20exercise%2C%C2%A0if%20mishandled%2C%20could%20rekindle%20old%20regional%20tensions%2C%20much%20like%20the%20linguistic%20and%20statehood%20agitations%20of%20the%20past.%20The%20challenge%20concerns%20fairness%2C%20trust%2C%20and%20the%20future%20of%20India's%20federal%20balance.%20Without%20broad%20consensus%2C%20every%20election%20could%20turn%20into%20a%20battle%20over%20legitimacy.%20Get%20it%20right%2C%20and%20India%20evolves.%20Get%20it%20wrong%2C%20and%20the%20cracks%20could%20run%20deep.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Aditya%20Sinha%20is%20a%20public%20policy%20professional.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742822700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2F7ko6i7hc_new-parliament-ani-new-lok-sabha-ani_625x300_01_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fdelimitation-dont-look-for-easy-answers-for-there-are-none-8000064%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20mishandled%2C%20the%20delimitation%20exercise%20could%20rekindle%20old%20regional%20tensions%2C%20much%20like%20the%20linguistic%20and%20statehood%20agitations%20of%20the%20past.%20India%20can't%20afford%20to%20get%20it%20wrong.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fdelimitation-dont-look-for-easy-answers-for-there-are-none-8000064%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Urban%20Company%20Cancels%20Service%20After%20Man%20Insists%20On%20Speaking%20Kannada%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20Bengaluru%20resident%20has%20taken%20to%20social%20media%20to%20express%20his%20disappointment%20with%20Urban%20Company%2C%20alleging%20that%20they%20cancelled%20his%20bathroom%20cleaning%20service%20after%20he%20requested%20their%20staff%20to%20communicate%20in%20Kannada.%20In%20a%20post%20on%20X%2C%20the%20user%20shared%20that%20he%C2%A0booked%20a%20bathroom%20cleaning%20service%2C%20and%20when%20the%20two%20workers%20arrived%2C%20he%20showed%20them%20the%20area%20that%20needed%20attention.%20However%2C%20one%20of%20the%20workers%20began%20speaking%20in%20a%20language%20the%20resident%20couldn't%20understand.%20When%20he%20politely%20requested%2C%20%26quot%3BKannada%2C%20please%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20conversation%20continued%20in%20the%20unfamiliar%20language%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20communication%20breakdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20attempt%20to%20bridge%20the%20communication%20gap%2C%20the%20workers%20called%20a%20supervisor%20who%20spoke%20Kannada.%20According%20to%20the%20resident%2C%20the%20supervisor%20claimed%20that%20the%20workers%20were%20uncomfortable%20because%20he%20insisted%20on%20communicating%20only%20in%20Kannada.%20This%20response%20allegedly%20led%20to%20the%20cancellation%20of%20the%20bathroom%20cleaning%20service%2C%20leaving%20the%20customer%20dismayed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSurprisingly%2C%20the%20person%20said%20it's%20difficult%20for%20their%20workers%20if%20the%20customer%20speaks%20only%20Kannada.%20I%20responded%2C%20''I%20haven't%20asked%20them%20to%20write%20poetry%20about%20my%20bathroom.%20Just%20clean%20and%20leave.%20What's%20the%20issue%3F''%20Then%20they%20called%20Urban%20Company's%20customer%20care%2C%20who%20also%20said%20she%20couldn't%20speak%20Kannada.%20Since%20I%20prefer%20to%20be%20served%20in%20my%20language%2C%20I%20didn't%20continue%20the%20call.%20After%20some%20more%20back%20and%20forth%2C%20they%20simply%20cancelled%20the%20booking%20and%20walked%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20user%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESee%20the%20post%20here%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%